<glossentry id="TTLAutoFlash-A65C7BF9" xml:lang="en">
<glossterm>TTL auto flash</glossterm>
<glossdef>The camera's light sensor measures flash illumination, as
reflected by the subject on the film and shuts off the flash where
measurement indicates a correct exposure. Because the sensor that
controls the flash receives light through the lens TTL auto flash
can be used for bounce flash photography, fill flash, multiple flash
photography, etc. An additional advantage of TTL auto flash is that
it enables you to use a wide range of aperture settings, while ensuring
correct exposure.</glossdef><?Pub Caret -1?>
</glossentry>
